  <div class="rules">
    <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>SHORT DESCRIPTION&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&ldquo;<strong>Wheel of Fortune</strong>&rdquo; is a very fast and simple live game with clear betting options.</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>GAME PROCESS</strong></p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">Presenter introduces the Wheel of Fortune, spins it counter-clockwise and then spins it clockwise with a light hand stroke. Only one spin is made during a draw except for cases when the spin must be repeated. Presenter&rsquo;s spin (and the draw) is valid if the wheel makes at least three (3) full spins clockwise. Full clockwise spins are counted by the spins counter and a green light is lit when the wheel makes three (3) full spins. The spin starts when the wheel starts spinning clockwise and the pointer leaves the sector where it was previously standing. The result of the draw is the sector&rsquo;s number or symbol where the pointer lands after the wheel stops turning;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">There is only one betting round and players can place their bets on all available outcomes for the upcoming draw. A betting round takes place between the game draws and lasts about four minutes. Draws of the game run every 5 minutes daily.</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>HOW TO PLACE A BET?</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Login to your account;</li>
    <li>Make a deposit to your account if necessary;</li>
    <li>Select a betting category and choose the outcome of the draw;&nbsp;</li>
    </ul>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive" src="http://wiki.betgames.tv/images/4/40/WoF_betting_options_EN.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="452" /></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <ul>
    <li>Enter your stake in the bet slip field &ldquo;<strong>Amount</strong>&rdquo;;&nbsp;</li>
    <li>Press the &ldquo;<strong>Place bet</strong>&rdquo; button;</li>
    </ul>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive" src="http://wiki.betgames.tv/images/1/1c/WoF_betting_slip_EN.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="452" /></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <ul>
    <li style="text-align: justify;">A message &ldquo;<strong>Bet successful</strong>&rdquo; will appear after your bet is placed.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive" src="http://wiki.betgames.tv/images/c/cf/WoF_betting_success_EN.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="653" /></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">The winnings are calculated by multiplying the stake by the odds. It's not possible to combine (parlay) LIVE GAMES bets. &nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">Each draw has a unique number and outcomes can be found on the &ldquo;<strong>Results</strong>&rdquo; page.&nbsp;</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive" src="http://wiki.betgames.tv/images/c/c0/WoF_results_EN.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="452" /></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p style="text-align: justify;">You can check your betting history on the &ldquo;<strong>Bet history</strong>&rdquo; page.</p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><img class="img-responsive" src="http://wiki.betgames.tv/images/7/73/WoF_bets_EN.jpg" alt="" width="720" height="452" /></p>
    <p>&nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>GAME RULES</strong></p>
    <p><strong>1. Terms:</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1.1. Wheel of Fortune &ndash; a round gaming device divided into nineteen (19) sectors which are separated by metal holders;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1.2. Sector &ndash; one out of nineteen (1/19) parts of the wheel numbered from one (1) to eighteen (18) or marked with a special symbol (a cup with a star). All sectors are of equal size;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1.3. Draw result &ndash; sector where the lower end of the pointer stops (closer to the center of the wheel). Results are determined according to fixed rules (see 2.8.);</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1.4. Pointer &ndash; a part of the gaming device (at the top middle of the wheel) which determines the result of the draw;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1.5. Odds &ndash; numerical expression which is multiplied by the player&rsquo;s stake to calculate the winnings. &nbsp;</p>
    <p><strong>2. Rules:&nbsp;</strong></p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.1. The game&rsquo;s presenter introduces the Wheel of Fortune, spins it counter-clockwise and then spins it clockwise with a light hand stroke;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.2. One Wheel of Fortune is used in the game;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.3. Only one spin is made during a draw except for cases when the spin must be repeated (see 4.2.);</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.4. Presenter&rsquo;s spin (and the draw) is valid if the wheel makes at least three (3) full spins clockwise;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.5. A turn starts when the presenter&rsquo;s spinned wheel starts spinning clockwise and the pointer leaves the sector where it was previously standing;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.6. The result of the draw is the sector&rsquo;s number or symbol where the pointer lands after the wheel stops turning;</p>
    <p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 2.7. Results for Wheel of Fortune: &nbsp;</p>
